content.description:
WHERE EAGLES DARE 5.10d ** (150') G

The obvious vertical crack left of center on the West face. Begins at the large chimney slot, exiting left then climbs the crack above to the 2 bolt anchor on top (staying right of the old eagles nest). Good climbing on somewhat crumbly rock.
content.protection: gear - a full range of cams and nuts
content.location:
The obvious vertical crack left of center on the West face.

Walk off to the west.

content.description:
TRAD GONE BAD 5.11a/A0 * (80') M (6b)

Begin 50' left and uphill from "Road to Nowhere". Climb the seam and finger crack till you can hand or foot traverse right, climb the face above to the headwall. A short A0 pull on the 2nd to last bolt gets you to a hard free move and the 2 bolt belay on the large ledge at mid-face.
content.location: Begin 50' left and uphill from "Road to Nowhere"

content.description:
TENDER FOOT 5.10a ** (115') M (8b)

At the far left side of the cliff, climb the lower slabs to the diagonal overhangs. Traverse left and continue up to the big ledge and shallow right facing corner in the broken upper face. Great climbing on somewhat questionable rock with great big holds. Take some small to medium stoppers.

Easy for the grade but a bit intimidating.
content.protection:
Mixed - 8 bolts plus some small to medium stoppers.

A single 60m rap is possible.
content.location: The steep corner/crack system at the far left end of the West face.

content.description:
STEPPIN' WOLF IN SHEEP'S CLOTHING 5.11d *** (55') M (2b, 1fn)

A short climb on the headwall at the very top of the west face. Beginning from the sloping ramp ("Broadway"), follow the obvious arching crack to the steep face above. Poor rests and a long reach near the top make for a challenging climb! Cold shut anchors are over the top.
content.protection: Gear needed for first half then 1 fixed nut and 2 fixed bolts get you to the top
content.location: On the upper headwall at the very top of the west face. Begin from the sloping ramp (Broadway).

content.description:
EAGLE SCOUT 5.11c/d ** (140') TR

Currently only has top anchors but would make a great mixed route (needing about 10 bolts). Climbs the face 10' left of the Eagle crack. Begin just right of the large diagonal corner at the loose flakes. Steep and reachy climbing offers a variety of strenuous moves to the cold shut anchors just below the top. Good rock up high.
content.location: On the left side of the West Face - between Tender Foot and Where Eagles Dare.
